sequenceDiagram
    title Producer-Driven Contract Testing

    participant CLI as CLI / HTTP Client
    participant Executor as Producer Executor
    participant RealAPI as Real API (Producer)
    participant Validator as Schema + Diff Validator

    note over CLI,Validator: Setup Phase
    CLI ->> Executor: Load scenarios (group / scenario file)
    CLI ->> Executor: Attach OpenAPI spec (--spec or spec_content)
    Executor -->> CLI: Executor ready

    note over Executor,RealAPI: Contract Execution Loop
    loop For each scenario × execution_times
        Executor ->> Executor: Build request\n(fuzz data + body fields → template params)
        Executor ->> RealAPI: Send HTTP request
        RealAPI -->> Executor: Real response

        Executor ->> Validator: Validate response body patterns\n(flat keys + JSONPath: $.order.id)
        Executor ->> Validator: Validate OpenAPI schema\n(missing fields, wrong types)
        Validator -->> Executor: Diff report\n(MissingFields, ValueMismatches, SchemaViolations)
    end

    note over CLI,Validator: Mutation Testing (--mutations flag)
    Executor ->> Executor: Generate mutations\n(null fields / boundary / format / security)
    loop For each mutation variant
        Executor ->> RealAPI: Send mutated request
        RealAPI -->> Executor: Response
        Executor ->> Executor: Assert robustness (expect 4xx)
    end

    note over CLI,Validator: Results
    Executor -->> CLI: ProducerContractResponse\n(Succeeded / Failed / Mismatched)
    CLI ->> CLI: Print colored results table
    CLI ->> CLI: Print coverage report\n(% paths covered, uncovered paths)

    alt All contracts pass
        CLI ->> CLI: Exit 0 — API backward compatible
    else Failures detected
        CLI ->> CLI: Print field-level diagnostics\n(error_details: which field, expected vs actual)
        CLI ->> CLI: Exit non-zero
    end
